    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-12-03T02:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-12-03T02:00:00-05:00" n="562"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d562">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.71247H/70: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Sydney</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Preston</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sydney</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-12-03T17:00:00+10:00"
                            >December 3, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received December 3—9:05 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Referring to my telegram of October 23, 11 a.m.,<note n="78" xml:id="d562fn78"
                        >Not printed.</note> enabling legislation introduced in Parliament today to
                    exclude American vessels from Tasman trade. Bill based on similar New Zealand
                    legislation. Probably no final action until after Christmas recess and
                    indications are it will pass by substantial majority. I will send copy of bill
                    as soon as received.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Preston</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
